  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 69-year-old man undergoes modified radical neck dissection for an oropharyngeal tumor. During the procedure, he requires multiple blood transfusions. Four hours after the surgery, examination shows that the right and left pupils do not constrict when a light is shone into the left eye. When light is shone into the right eye, both pupils constrict. Fundoscopic examination shows no abnormalities. Which of the following is the most likely location of the lesion?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Optic nerve"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Pretectal nuclei"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Superior cervical ganglion"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Ophthalmic nerve"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Edinger-Westphal nucleus"
        },
        {
          "id": 6,
          "text": "Lateral geniculate body"
        },
        {
          "id": 7,
          "text": "Ciliary ganglion"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>A <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qO0CtT&anker=Z055fc070ac6cc728b4c2e7819c10e36d\" data-learningcard-id=\"qO0CtT\" data-anker=\"Z055fc070ac6cc728b4c2e7819c10e36d\" data-section-id=\"Y9XnNZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"qfYCMo\">relative afferent pupillary defect</a> typically occurs because of <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>unilateral damage to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cp0aoS&anker=Zafbc538c70facdb76c5c65393ad05dbb\" data-learningcard-id=\"cp0aoS\" data-anker=\"Zafbc538c70facdb76c5c65393ad05dbb\" data-section-id=\"AvcRce0\" data-sememe-id=\"zZcrVa0\">retina</a> and/or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z10563771c184f2ce534a98372dc51b89\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z10563771c184f2ce534a98372dc51b89\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"kqamAl\">optic nerve</a></b></span> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z10563771c184f2ce534a98372dc51b89\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z10563771c184f2ce534a98372dc51b89\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"kqamAl\">CN II</a>). In this patient damage to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z10563771c184f2ce534a98372dc51b89\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z10563771c184f2ce534a98372dc51b89\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"kqamAl\">optic nerve</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z10563771c184f2ce534a98372dc51b89\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z10563771c184f2ce534a98372dc51b89\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"kqamAl\">CN II</a>) due to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=VP0GdT&anker=Zbc05e544d46e794a60ac9ce9ec6883af\" data-learningcard-id=\"VP0GdT\" data-anker=\"Zbc05e544d46e794a60ac9ce9ec6883af\" data-section-id=\"k9cmne0\" data-sememe-id=\"WQ0PEf\">ischemic</a> optic neuropathy has resulted in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qO0CtT&anker=Z055fc070ac6cc728b4c2e7819c10e36d\" data-learningcard-id=\"qO0CtT\" data-anker=\"Z055fc070ac6cc728b4c2e7819c10e36d\" data-section-id=\"Y9XnNZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"qfYCMo\">RAPD</a>. Complete damage to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z10563771c184f2ce534a98372dc51b89\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z10563771c184f2ce534a98372dc51b89\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"kqamAl\">CN II</a> would also result in loss of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cp0aoS&anker=Z8473446b734702b73ac2972b7bbf7bf7\" data-learningcard-id=\"cp0aoS\" data-anker=\"Z8473446b734702b73ac2972b7bbf7bf7\" data-section-id=\"Dvc1Xe0\" data-sememe-id=\"fm1kUh0\">vision</a> on the affected side.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_661e99df0344a2.88916484.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>The afferent pathway (blue tract) is initiated when light hits the retina:<br/>- Retinal photoreceptors → ipsilateral optic nerve → nuclei of bilateral pretectal areas (nasal fibers of the optic nerve cross to the contralateral side at the optic chiasma)</p><p>The efferent pathway (green tract) transmits neural impulses to the iris sphincter muscle:<br/>- Nuclei of pretectal area → bilateral Edinger Westphal nuclei (parasympathetic preganglionic nucleus of the oculomotor nerve) → bilateral oculomotor nerves (synapse at the ciliary ganglion) → bilateral iris sphincter muscle (and ciliary muscle) → bilateral pupillary constriction (and accomodation).</p><p>Shining a light into one eye causes constriction of the ipsilateral pupil (direct pupillary reflex) as well as that of the contralateral pupil (indirect or consensual pupillary reflex).</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>The <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=b70H4h&anker=Ze747de0497048b0416250ad9c1f6fcf3\" data-learningcard-id=\"b70H4h\" data-anker=\"Ze747de0497048b0416250ad9c1f6fcf3\" data-section-id=\"G71BMR0\" data-sememe-id=\"ugXpCx\">pretectal region</a></span> receives afferent fibers of the <span data-sememe-id=\"Tm16Uh0\">pupillary</span> pathway from both eyes. Unilateral damage can, therefore, be compensated by the innervation from the <span data-sememe-id=\"qvXCaZ0\">contralateral</span> side. Bilateral damage to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=b70H4h&anker=Ze747de0497048b0416250ad9c1f6fcf3\" data-learningcard-id=\"b70H4h\" data-anker=\"Ze747de0497048b0416250ad9c1f6fcf3\" data-section-id=\"G71BMR0\" data-sememe-id=\"ugXpCx\">pretectal region</a>, on the other hand, manifests with absent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qO0CtT&anker=Z6ad04796bf03283e7a67af744426d446\" data-learningcard-id=\"qO0CtT\" data-anker=\"Z6ad04796bf03283e7a67af744426d446\" data-section-id=\"Rvcl-V0\" data-sememe-id=\"Sdby6s\">direct pupillary reflexes</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qO0CtT&anker=Z50b7c6f77168c7e75a9b067c4f70397a\" data-learningcard-id=\"qO0CtT\" data-anker=\"Z50b7c6f77168c7e75a9b067c4f70397a\" data-section-id=\"Rvcl-V0\" data-sememe-id=\"hdbcps\">indirect pupillary reflexes</a> in both eyes.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Damage to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=560ilS&anker=Z6a34184c2822baf5103edf59d89f97c2\" data-learningcard-id=\"560ilS\" data-anker=\"Z6a34184c2822baf5103edf59d89f97c2\" data-section-id=\"8wcOke0\" data-sememe-id=\"pQXLCB\">superior cervical ganglion</a> and its <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=560ilS&anker=Ze80abab5d42f0490f5ab74735e7e76da\" data-learningcard-id=\"560ilS\" data-anker=\"Ze80abab5d42f0490f5ab74735e7e76da\" data-section-id=\"8wcOke0\" data-sememe-id=\"-5XD5A\">sympathetic</a> nerve fibers is a potential complication of radical deep <span data-sememe-id=\"wrchjd0\">neck dissection</span>. However, patients in such cases would present with <span data-sememe-id=\"3JXSF_\">ipsilateral</span> <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qO0CtT&anker=Z0e51d0270de0f8ebe0a316768eda24de\" data-learningcard-id=\"qO0CtT\" data-anker=\"Z0e51d0270de0f8ebe0a316768eda24de\" data-section-id=\"Rvcl-V0\" data-sememe-id=\"gg0Fu2\">miosis</a></span> and other symptoms of <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ui0bIf&anker=Z20f48a92c69fed649f5f53436bfd2c09\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ui0bIf\" data-anker=\"Z20f48a92c69fed649f5f53436bfd2c09\" data-sememe-id=\"Jl0sBT\">Horner syndrome</a></span> (e.g. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lO0vsT&anker=Zac7d41bbe736ff1d9898855bfa4b7d1f\" data-learningcard-id=\"lO0vsT\" data-anker=\"Zac7d41bbe736ff1d9898855bfa4b7d1f\" data-section-id=\"2wXTRZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"uAaplM\">ptosis</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ui0bIf&anker=Zbfc0ef1ee5cdc6ccfd71ba755eaa687e\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ui0bIf\" data-anker=\"Zbfc0ef1ee5cdc6ccfd71ba755eaa687e\" data-section-id=\"6vaja5\" data-sememe-id=\"eLXx9A\">anhidrosis</a>).</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Damage to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z12a9bd48735744781346551878040e8f\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z12a9bd48735744781346551878040e8f\" data-section-id=\"OncIt10\" data-sememe-id=\"muXV7-\">ophthalmic nerve</a> (a branch of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z4369db0d59ac05b34ecb586a742eab31\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z4369db0d59ac05b34ecb586a742eab31\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"MqaM_l\">CN V</a>) results in absent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Ze63e4f9b8147b71d6fd0567e525cc690\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Ze63e4f9b8147b71d6fd0567e525cc690\" data-section-id=\"xAXEN00\" data-sememe-id=\"-UYDfo\">corneal reflex</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Z12a9bd48735744781346551878040e8f\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Z12a9bd48735744781346551878040e8f\" data-section-id=\"OncIt10\" data-sememe-id=\"muXV7-\">Ophthalmic nerve</a> damage can also result in sensory deficits in the periorbital region and the <span data-sememe-id=\"3JXSF_\">ipsilateral</span> forehead. The <span data-sememe-id=\"Tm16Uh0\">pupillary</span> response would not be affected.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Damage to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=560ilS&anker=Za4884432bfd8263f7f79f9b0cb0af287\" data-learningcard-id=\"560ilS\" data-anker=\"Za4884432bfd8263f7f79f9b0cb0af287\" data-section-id=\"uwcpke0\" data-sememe-id=\"7SX4aB\">parasympathetic</a> <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=560ilS&anker=Z1c487a2e52dab41d52f82baf28bcbc00\" data-learningcard-id=\"560ilS\" data-anker=\"Z1c487a2e52dab41d52f82baf28bcbc00\" data-section-id=\"uwcpke0\" data-sememe-id=\"jhX_dB\">Edinger-Westphal nucleus</a></span>, which contains the efferent <span data-sememe-id=\"Tm16Uh0\">pupillary</span> response pathway, leads to absent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qO0CtT&anker=Z404ae0ae4296f4475cf9d11eb43230e4\" data-learningcard-id=\"qO0CtT\" data-anker=\"Z404ae0ae4296f4475cf9d11eb43230e4\" data-section-id=\"Rvcl-V0\" data-sememe-id=\"lzYvG7\">pupillary reflex</a> (direct and indirect) in the <span data-sememe-id=\"3JXSF_\">ipsilateral</span> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cp0aoS&anker=Z59567810bfa0760228f174d87f18477b\" data-learningcard-id=\"cp0aoS\" data-anker=\"Z59567810bfa0760228f174d87f18477b\">eye</a>, while the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qO0CtT&anker=Z404ae0ae4296f4475cf9d11eb43230e4\" data-learningcard-id=\"qO0CtT\" data-anker=\"Z404ae0ae4296f4475cf9d11eb43230e4\" data-section-id=\"Rvcl-V0\" data-sememe-id=\"lzYvG7\">pupillary reflex</a> (direct and indirect) in the <span data-sememe-id=\"qvXCaZ0\">contralateral</span> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cp0aoS&anker=Z59567810bfa0760228f174d87f18477b\" data-learningcard-id=\"cp0aoS\" data-anker=\"Z59567810bfa0760228f174d87f18477b\">eye</a> remains intact.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>F) INCORRECT:</h4>Damage to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-60DnS&anker=Z4e8bdc78cb78860c3454f3b91cce99d9\" data-learningcard-id=\"-60DnS\" data-anker=\"Z4e8bdc78cb78860c3454f3b91cce99d9\" data-section-id=\"Fvcgbe0\" data-sememe-id=\"3QXSDB\">lateral geniculate body</a> leads to <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=FO0g8T&anker=Zc8405b2bd5dc55d31e85de549831a430\" data-learningcard-id=\"FO0g8T\" data-anker=\"Zc8405b2bd5dc55d31e85de549831a430\" data-section-id=\"j9X_MZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"ZXbZ9H\">homonymous hemianopia</a></span> of the <span data-sememe-id=\"qvXCaZ0\">contralateral</span> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aM0QMg&anker=Zc981707794a24bd79fce06860fcdc2b3\" data-learningcard-id=\"aM0QMg\" data-anker=\"Zc981707794a24bd79fce06860fcdc2b3\" data-section-id=\"7_X4p00\" data-sememe-id=\"U8XbN-\">visual field</a>. The <span data-sememe-id=\"Tm16Uh0\">pupillary</span> response pathway does not pass through the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-60DnS&anker=Z4e8bdc78cb78860c3454f3b91cce99d9\" data-learningcard-id=\"-60DnS\" data-anker=\"Z4e8bdc78cb78860c3454f3b91cce99d9\" data-section-id=\"Fvcgbe0\" data-sememe-id=\"3QXSDB\">lateral geniculate body</a>, and so <span data-sememe-id=\"Tm16Uh0\">pupillary</span> reactions to light would not be affected.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_5f86d0bf2220b.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>1. Retina: The visual pathway begins at the retina. The temporal field of vision is projected onto the nasal portion of the retina and the nasal field of vision is projected onto the temporal portion of the retina.<br/>2. Optic nerves: The axons of the retinal ganglion cells merge to form the optic nerve, which carries the nasal and temporal fibers of the ipsilateral retina.<br/>3. Optic chiasm: The two optic nerves meet at the optic chiasm, where the nasal fibers of each retina cross over to the contralateral side. The temporal fibers remain uncrossed.<br/>4. Optic tracts: Each optic tract carries contralateral nasal fibers and ipsilateral temporal fibers (i.e., the right optic tract carries the nasal fibers of the left eye and the temporal fibers of the right eye). I.e., each optic tract carries the contralateral visual field of each eye.<br/>5. Lateral geniculate nucleus (LGN): The optic tracts synapse onto the ipsilateral LGN.<br/>6. Optic radiation: consists of neurons that carry visual information from the ipsilateral LGN to the ipsilateral primary visual cortex<br/>7. Primary visual cortex: The visual pathway terminates at the primary visual cortex, which is located at the posterior aspect of the occipital lobe. It is responsible for the perception of sight. The right visual cortex receives visual information from the right nasal field and the left temporal field of vision, i.e. the left visual field of each eye.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>G) INCORRECT:</h4>Damage to the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=560ilS&anker=Z9cb5f0eb5847f6429814302ac753839d\" data-learningcard-id=\"560ilS\" data-anker=\"Z9cb5f0eb5847f6429814302ac753839d\" data-section-id=\"uwcpke0\" data-sememe-id=\"ihXJdB\">ciliary ganglion</a></span>, which contains the efferent fibers of the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tR0XKf&anker=Zf93de13b5536af7dcc148ee0b926bc14\" data-learningcard-id=\"tR0XKf\" data-anker=\"Zf93de13b5536af7dcc148ee0b926bc14\" data-section-id=\"lncvt10\" data-sememe-id=\"lqavAl\">CN III</a></span>, results in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3u0SI3&anker=Zd7f9061edc1020a411ebccbb319b47ec\" data-learningcard-id=\"3u0SI3\" data-anker=\"Zd7f9061edc1020a411ebccbb319b47ec\" data-section-id=\"WVdPtK0\" data-sememe-id=\"4MW3KN0\">paresis</a> of the <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cp0aoS&anker=Z45591d4af9cde7dee17eae2dd79ab02f\" data-learningcard-id=\"cp0aoS\" data-anker=\"Z45591d4af9cde7dee17eae2dd79ab02f\" data-section-id=\"AvcRce0\" data-sememe-id=\"XOb9IF\">sphincter pupillae</a></span> muscle. Thus, damage to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=560ilS&anker=Z9cb5f0eb5847f6429814302ac753839d\" data-learningcard-id=\"560ilS\" data-anker=\"Z9cb5f0eb5847f6429814302ac753839d\" data-section-id=\"uwcpke0\" data-sememe-id=\"ihXJdB\">ciliary ganglion</a> would manifest with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qO0CtT&anker=Z7c2c58011b8475657d8daefa023acf40\" data-learningcard-id=\"qO0CtT\" data-anker=\"Z7c2c58011b8475657d8daefa023acf40\" data-section-id=\"Rvcl-V0\" data-sememe-id=\"ig0JE2\">mydriasis</a> and absent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qO0CtT&anker=Z404ae0ae4296f4475cf9d11eb43230e4\" data-learningcard-id=\"qO0CtT\" data-anker=\"Z404ae0ae4296f4475cf9d11eb43230e4\" data-section-id=\"Rvcl-V0\" data-sememe-id=\"lzYvG7\">pupillary reflex</a> (both direct and consensual) in the <span data-sememe-id=\"3JXSF_\">ipsilateral</span> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cp0aoS&anker=Z59567810bfa0760228f174d87f18477b\" data-learningcard-id=\"cp0aoS\" data-anker=\"Z59567810bfa0760228f174d87f18477b\">eye</a>, and normal <span data-sememe-id=\"Tm16Uh0\">pupillary</span> response in the unaffected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cp0aoS&anker=Z59567810bfa0760228f174d87f18477b\" data-learningcard-id=\"cp0aoS\" data-anker=\"Z59567810bfa0760228f174d87f18477b\">eye</a>.</div>",
      "hint": "The patient presents with a relative afferent pupillary defect (RAPD). Given his need for multiple blood transfusions during surgery, the patient presumably had an episode of intraoperative blood loss. This blood loss could have resulted in hypotension and subsequent ischemic damage to a CNS structure involved in the pupillary response.",
